================================================================================
Dependency license posture
================================================================================

The three packages in this repository (fb-assist, fb-os, pps-pipeline) have a
deliberately light, permissively-licensed dependency surface. The runnable core
of each package is stdlib-only and degrades gracefully when optional heavy
dependencies are absent.

Optional Python dependencies and their licenses (all permissive):

  presidio-analyzer / presidio-anonymizer   MIT        (PII detection)
  gliner                                     Apache-2.0 (NER PII detection)
  detect-secrets                             Apache-2.0 (secret detection)
  spaCy + en_core_web_sm                     MIT        (NER backbone)
  mcp (Model Context Protocol SDK)           MIT        (in-session server)
  anthropic (SDK)                            MIT        (claude-repro API surface)
  faster-whisper                             MIT        (optional voice confirm)
  jsonschema                                 MIT        (schema validation)
  sentence-transformers / bertopic / hdbscan MIT/BSD    (optional fb-os clustering)

External binaries (invoked only if already installed; NEITHER bundled NOR a
dependency):

  gitleaks    MIT      — optional secret scanner; shelled out to if on PATH.
  trufflehog  AGPL-3.0 — optional secret scanner; shelled out to ONLY as a
                         pre-installed external binary. It is never bundled,
                         never imported, and never a Python/packaging
                         dependency, so its AGPL terms do not attach to this
                         work. The regex secret floor + gitleaks cover the
                         secret-detection layer without it.

================================================================================
A note on the test corpus
================================================================================

The large test fixtures (fb-assist/tests/fixtures/sample-mid.jsonl and
sample-large.jsonl) are FULLY SYNTHETIC, deterministically generated at test
time by tests/fixtures/generate_fixtures.py. No real Claude Code session, user
prompt, file content, path, or credential ships in this repository. See
`make scrub-gate`.
